      <bioghist id="aspace_34f0aae8c5f8a247b0eb12945867e929">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Amos L. Williams, physician, was born on January 7, 1811, in Lebanon, Connecticut. Williams received diplomas from Jefferson Medical School, Philadelphia and Yale Medical School, New Haven. He represented the town of Brookfield, Connecticut, at the state legislature in 1883 and served the town as medical examiner, postmaster, and registrar. His professional life in Brookfield extended over sixty-three years. He died on April 16, 1896, in Brookfield Center, Connecticut.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_e41a9dd10cf06aa2a7f9da1d8c4ab22e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Notebooks, financial records, and miscellanea of Amos L. Williams, a physician in Brookfield, Connecticut. Includes notes on lectures of Eli Ives, William Tully, and others.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
